{
  "texts": [
    "C. Decentralized and Self-Governing Agent EcosystemsThe shift toward decentralized IoA architectures, where smart city agents, supply chain robots, and energy grids operate without relying on a central authority, requires self-governance mechanisms that mimic biological ecosystems.",
    "Future ecosystems should enable agents to self-organize through decentralized consensus mechanisms, adaptive blockchain sharding, and bio-inspired swarm intelligence.However, scalable consensus protocols face a paradox [145]: full decentralization ensures robustness but struggles with realtime coordination at scale.",
    "Another issue is conflict resolution in emergent systems.",
    "For instance, a delivery robot may prioritize speed while a sidewalk robot emphasizes pedestrian safety.",
    "Besides, decentralized coordination may inadvertently optimize for local efficiency at the expense of global stability."
  ]
}